<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-02-14T00:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-02-14T00:35:00-05:00" n="556" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d556">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">511.4 A 2/275: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Persia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Murray</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Teheran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-02-14T09:00:00+03:25"><hi rend="italic">February 14,
                                        1925—9 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received February 14—9:33
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>11. Department’s telegraphic instructions Nos. 4, February 7, 3 p.m., and
                            7, February 12, 4 p.m. I am delivering to Persian Government today note
                            on opium containing substance of first-mentioned telegram as modified.
                            My British colleague has been notified of action I am taking.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Murray</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>